ResourceHeader.ResourceName: Ulysses Heliosphere Instrument for Spectral, Composition, and Anisotropy at Low Energies (HISCALE) LEFS150 MFSA, Solar Wind Frame, Sectored Z>1 Ion Fluxes, Daily Averages
ResourceHeader.Description: Daily-averaged sectored Z>1 ion fluxes from the MF Spectrum Analyzer of the Ulysses/HISCALE LEFS150 instrument. All energies thresholds take into account the incident particle type, shielding, and inactive dead-layer of the solid state detector. All fluxes are background corrected and are in the solar wind rest frame.
ResourceHeader.Acknowledgement: Thomas P. Armstrong, Fundamental Technologies, LLC

AccessURL.Name: Ulysses HISCALE Daily-Averaged
AccessURL.Description: Parent directory containing the Daily-averaged fluxes for the Ulysses/HISCALE instrument for the entire mission.
